  <a name="mmi-35278"></a>
  



      <div id="mmi-35278" class="scrolling-text-module colspan-4 rag measurable magic-module" data-event-category="magic_module/scrolling_text_module/35278" data-event-label="Scrolling Text Module 35278 (3/14)" data-instance-id="35278" data-id="98375">                  <div class="scrolling-text-module__inner" style="max-height: 240.0em" tabindex="0">
    
    The Yale School of Art is pleased to announce three new full-time faculty appointments in the area of graduate study in Graphic Design. Yeju Choi, Critic in Graphic Design since 2012 and 2009 MFA alum, joins as full-time Core Faculty; Andrew Walsh-Lister, 2012 alum in Graphic Design, has been appointed Critic; and Alvin Ashiatey, 2022 alum of the program and former fellow at the Center for Collaborative Arts &amp; Media, has been appointed Lecturer.
</div>

